===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
A sieve next to an axe; its original meaning was "to divide/break with an axe" and, according to Xu Shen, it was synonym of 析. The original meaning is still preserved in the character 撕.

===Etymology 1===
Cognate with {{och-l|此|this}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

STEDT compares {{och-l|此}} and {{och-l|斯}} to {{cog|sit-tan-pro|*si||this}}.

